## What NOT To Do

- **Do not write implementation code before writing a failing test.** TDD is mandatory.
- **Do not submit code below 95% test coverage** in any module.
- **Do not write untyped Python code.** Every function, method, and variable must have type annotations. `mypy --strict` must pass.
- **Do not skip regression tests** when fixing bugs â€” every fix needs a test proving the bug existed.
- **Do not silently defer work.** If you discover bugs, tech debt, or out-of-scope items, create a GitHub Issue (or configured tracker item). Every `TODO`/`FIXME` in code must reference an issue number.
